oai_dc:dc.dc:title: IMPACT LOADING AND DYNAMIC RESPONSE OF CAISSON BREAKWATERS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Oumeraci, H.
Partenscky, H.W.
Kohlhase, S.
Klammer, P.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: breakwater
impact loading
dynamic response
caisson
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The results of large-scale model tests on impact loading and dynamic response of a caisson breakwater are presented. Hydraulic model tests are performed in which the impact loading is induced by breaking waves on the structure. Horizontal impact forces, uplift forces and the related overturning moments are determined. The transmissibility of the impact loads and the accelerations of the structure are investigated (dynamic response).. The hydraulic model tests are supplemented by pendulum tests on the same caisson breakwater model used in the hydraulic model tests in order to determine the characteristics of the structural model itself. The added mass of water oscillating with the structure, the stiffness of the foundation and the damping ratio are evaluated from these tests.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 23 (1992): Proceedings of 23rd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Venice, Italy, 1992.
